## Tech Stack — What We're Adding

| Library | Purpose | Why This One? |
|---------|---------|---------------|
| **Zustand** | Global state management | Lightweight (1KB), no boilerplate, no Context wrappers. Perfect for auth state, user data, subscription info |
| **TanStack Query** (React Query) | Server state (API caching) | **Already installed** (`@tanstack/react-query` v5.83.0 in package.json). Handles fetching, caching, refetching, loading/error states automatically |
| **Axios** | HTTP client | Cleaner API than fetch, interceptors for JWT, automatic JSON parsing |
| **Firebase** (client SDK) | Google sign-in popup | `signInWithPopup(GoogleAuthProvider)` → get ID token → send to backend |

### What is TanStack Query?

> [!NOTE]
> **TanStack Query** (formerly React Query) manages **server state** — data that lives on your backend. Think of it as a smart cache layer between your UI and API.
>
> **Without TanStack Query:** You write `useEffect` + `useState` + loading/error states manually for every API call. Stale data. No caching. No refetching.
>
> **With TanStack Query:** You write one hook like `useQuery({ queryKey: ['scans'], queryFn: fetchScans })` and get: loading state, error state, cached data, automatic refetch on focus, background updates, optimistic UI — all for free.
>
> **Key concepts:**
> - `useQuery` → READ data (GET requests) — fetches, caches, refetches automatically
> - `useMutation` → WRITE data (POST/PATCH/DELETE) — handles loading, error, and invalidates cache after success
> - `queryKey` → unique cache key (e.g. `['scans', scanId]`) — TanStack knows when to refetch
>
> You already have it installed. We're just writing the hooks.

### Zustand vs TanStack Query — Who Handles What?

```
┌───────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐
│                    ZUSTAND (Client State)              │
│  • Auth token (JWT)                                    │
│  • Is user logged in?                                  │
│  • User object (name, email, plan)                     │
│  • Logout function                                     │
│  • These rarely change — local, synchronous state      │
└───────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘

┌───────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐
│              TANSTACK QUERY (Server State)             │
│  • Scan history list (GET /api/scans)                  │
│  • Scan result details (GET /api/scans/:id)            │
│  • Dishes list (GET /api/scans/:id/dishes)             │
│  • Subscription usage (GET /api/subscription/usage)    │
│  • These change on the server — cached, refetchable    │
└───────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘
```

