- Fetch `recentScans` using `useRecentScans()` hook
- Fetch `usage` using `useSubscription()` hook
- If user has scans → show dashboard with latest scan data
- If user has NO scans yet → show "empty state" CTA: "Scan your first menu!"
- Pass real data down as props to child components:

**Dashboard components that change:**

| Component | Current | After |
|-----------|---------|-------|
| `StatsCards.tsx` | Hardcoded `24`, `8`, `10`, `6` | Accept `scan` prop → show `scan.healthyCount`, etc. |
| `HealthChart.tsx` | Hardcoded chart data array | Accept `scan` prop → compute chart from dish categories |
| `AIInsights.tsx` | Hardcoded 3 insights | Accept `recommendations` prop OR generate from scan data |
| `TopRecommendations.tsx` | Hardcoded 3 items with Unsplash images | Accept `recommendations` prop → show real recommended dishes |
| `MenuItemsTable.tsx` | Hardcoded 5 menu items | Accept `dishes` prop → show first 5 dishes from latest scan |
| `ScanLimitIndicator.tsx` | Hardcoded | Accept `usage` prop → show real scansUsed/scansLimit |

> [!IMPORTANT]
> **Dashboard design decision:** The current dashboard shows data for ONE scan (the latest). When the user has no scans yet, we show a prominent "Scan your first menu" empty state. When they have scans, the dashboard auto-selects the most recent completed scan.

