## Open Questions

> [!IMPORTANT]
> **1. Firebase Client Config:** Your `.env` only has `VITE_FIREBASE_APIKEY`. For the Firebase client SDK to work, we also need `VITE_FIREBASE_AUTH_DOMAIN` and `VITE_FIREBASE_PROJECT_ID`. Do you have these from Firebase Console?

> [!IMPORTANT]
> **2. Stripe Checkout Success URL:** After Stripe checkout completes, where should Stripe redirect the user? Options:
> - **Option A:** `/dashboard` (simple, just redirect home)
> - **Option B:** `/checkout/success?session_id=xxx` (dedicated page that verifies the session and shows a success message)
> - I recommend **Option B** since the backend has `GET /subscription/success?session_id=` endpoint for verification.

> [!IMPORTANT]
> **3. Dashboard — What to show when user has zero scans?** Options:
> - **Option A:** Empty state with big CTA "Scan your first menu!"
> - **Option B:** Show the dashboard layout but with zeros and a prominent upload prompt
> - I recommend **Option A** — cleaner first-time experience.
